This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image contour detection and segmentation using Convolutional Neural Networks. The paper also mentions the use of multiscale oriented contours and region hierarchies, which are common techniques in computer vision. 

The paper also involves machine learning techniques, such as CNNs, which are commonly used in the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). 

The paper's focus on improving performance and accuracy through novel techniques suggests that it may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. 

The use of sparse boundary representation for hierarchical segmentation may suggest that the paper could also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. 

Finally, the paper's use of datasets and evaluation metrics commonly used in Multimedia (cs.MM) may suggest that it could also belong to this sub-category.
